ation":0.72,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The dictionary-based fallback returns the correct pre-stored translation for phrases that exist in the SQLite database.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure boundary is repository + SQLite query/schema mapping, not just pure lookup logic. Unit mocking DB can miss SQL/schema/encoding mismatches. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: SQLite/local DB is explicitly Integration-level local infra; no need for real network/subprocess; no model-quality dependence.","test_description":"Use a real test SQLite database with seeded phrase rows; invoke fallback translator through service/repository boundary and assert exact match to stored translation for known phrases.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The quality tracking comparison correctly computes edit distance between primary and fallback outputs and stores the metric.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior combines algorithm correctness and persistence side effect. Minimum real-failure boundary is computation + metric storage wiring; unit-only tests could miss persistence mapping/transaction bugs. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: no required OS/network/subprocess behavior; no dependence on real AI output quality (fixed strings suffice). Rejected Agentic because behavior text is deterministic edit-distance computation, not judgment quality.","test_description":"Call the quality-tracking path with fixed primary/fallback strings with known edit distances, then verify persisted metric record in test DB matches expected value and links to the correct translation request.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When both translators are availa